{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866996006,"sessionID":"ses_28614b83affeyVWDYwcMvR6UKe","part":{"id":"prt_d79ebd78f001xaGDMEWj0vq86I","messageID":"msg_d79eba6a10013Z1gFa5Irc35Kw","sessionID":"ses_28614b83affeyVWDYwcMvR6UKe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0f409b5186c94662bf8ff0d2a9e24b89","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-007 |\n8: | Module | pkg/workloadmanager |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: 实现一个 Kubernetes Reconciler 控制器，用于管理 `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API 组下的自定义资源：\n17: \n18: - **AgentRuntime**: 管理 Agent 运行时实例的生命周期\n19: - **CodeInterpreter**: 管理代码解释器实例的生命周期\n20: \n21: 控制器将：\n22: 1. 监听 CRD 资源的创建、更新、删除事件\n23: 2. 根据 CR spec 协调实际状态向期望状态收敛\n24: 3. 管理底层 Pod、Service、ConfigMap 等工作负载资源\n25: 4. 更新 CR status 以反映当前状态\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n30: \n31: ### 2.1 In Scope\n32: \n33: 1. **Controller 框架搭建**\n34:    - 使用 `controller-runtime` 框架 (sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime)\n35:    - 集成 client-go 生成的客户端代码\n36:    - 实现 Reconcile 循环\n37: \n38: 2. **AgentRuntime 控制器**\n39:    - 监听 AgentRuntime CR 的变更\n40:    - 创建/更新/删除关联的 Kubernetes 资源 (Pod, Service, ConfigMap, Secret)\n41:    - 状态同步：Phase, Conditions, PodStatus, Endpoint 等\n42:    - 支持多副本部署策略\n43: \n44: 3. **CodeInterpreter 控制器**\n45:    - 监听 CodeInterpreter CR 的变更\n46:    - 管理解释器容器的生命周期\n47:    - 状态同步：Phase, Conditions, ResourceUsage 等\n48: \n49: 4. **通用功能**\n50:    - Event 记录 (Normal/Warning)\n51:    - Finalizer 处理 (资源清理)\n52:    - OwnerReference 设置 (级联删除)\n53:    - 领导选举 (Leader Election) 支持多实例部署\n54: \n55: ### 2.2 Out of Scope\n56: \n57: - Webhook (Validating/Mutating) - 由独立 AR 处理\n58: - CRD 定义本身 - 假设已存在\n59: - 具体业务逻辑 (Agent 执行、解释器逻辑) - 由其他模块处理\n60: - 监控指标暴露 - 由独立 AR 处理\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n65: \n66: ### 3.1 新增文件\n67: \n68: ```\n69: pkg/workloadmanager/\n70: ├── controller.go              # 控制器入口，注册 Manager\n71: ├── agentruntime_controller.go # AgentRuntime Reconciler 实现\n72: ├── codeinterpreter_controller.go # CodeInterpreter Reconciler 实现\n73: ├── reconciler.go              # 通用 Reconciler 辅助函数\n74: ├── status.go                  # 状态更新辅助函数\n75: ├── resource_builder.go        # Kubernetes 资源构建器\n76: ├── predicates.go              # Event 过滤谓词\n77: └── suite_test.go              # 控制器集成测试\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### 3.2 依赖关系\n81: \n82: ```\n83: pkg/workloadmanager\n84:     ├── github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go (已生成)\n85:     ├── sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime (需引入)\n86:     ├── k8s.io/api\n87:     ├── k8s.io/apimachinery\n88:     └── k8s.io/client-go\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### 3.3 与现有模块交互\n92: \n93: | 模块 | 交互方式 |\n94: |------|----------|\n95: | pkg/apis/runtime | 读取 CR 类型定义 |\n96: | client-go | 使用生成的 Clientset、Informer、Lister |\n97: | cmd/manager | 作为控制器入口点启动 |\n98: \n99: ### 3.4 风险与缓解\n100: \n101: | 风险 | 影响 | 缓解措施 |\n102: |------|------|----------|\n103: | 控制器重启导致短暂不可用 | Medium | 使用 Leader Election 确保单实例 |\n104: | CRD 版本兼容性 | Low | 使用 apiVersion 检查 + conversion webhook |\n105: | 大规模资源性能问题 | Medium | 使用 Informer 缓存 + WorkQueue 限流 |\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n110: \n111: ### 4.1 方案 A: controller-runtime (推荐)\n112: \n113: **实现方式**: 使用 sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime 框架\n114: \n115: **优点**:\n116: - Kubernetes 官方推荐方案\n117: - 内置 Informer、WorkQueue、Leader Election\n118: - 与 kubebuilder 生态兼容\n119: - 社区活跃，文档完善\n120: - 原生支持 webhook\n121: \n122: **缺点**:\n123: - 框架较重，学习曲线稍陡\n124: - 调试复杂度高\n125: \n126: ### 4.2 方案 B: client-go 原生实现\n127: \n128: **实现方式**: 使用 client-go 的 Informer + WorkQueue 手写控制器\n129: \n130: **优点**:\n131: - 完全控制实现细节\n132: - 无额外依赖\n133: - 更轻量\n134: \n135: **缺点**:\n136: - 需要手写大量样板代码\n137: - 需要自己实现 Leader Election\n138: - 维护成本高\n139: - 与社区最佳实践脱节\n140: \n141: ### 4.3 方案 C: KUDO\n142: \n143: **实现方式**: 使用 KUDO (Kubernetes Universal Declarative Operator)\n144: \n145: **优点**:\n146: - 声明式操作定义\n147: - 内置状态机\n148: \n149: **缺点**:\n150: - 项目已停止维护\n151: - 学习成本高\n152: - 不适合简单控制器\n153: \n154: ### 4.4 方案选择\n155: \n156: **选择方案 A (controller-runtime)**\n157: \n158: 理由:\n159: 1. 官方推荐，社区支持好\n160: 2. 与现有 client-go 生成的代码无缝集成\n161: 3. 为后续 webhook、monitor 集成铺路\n162: 4. 降低维护成本\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## 5. 设计要点\n167: \n168: ### 5.1 Reconcile 循环伪代码\n169: \n170: ```go\n171: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error) {\n172:     // 1. 获取 CR\n173:     ar := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n174:     if err := r.Client.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, ar); err != nil {\n175:         return ctrl.Result{}, client.IgnoreNotFound(err)\n176:     }\n177: \n178:     // 2. 检查 DeletionTimestamp (Finalizer 处理)\n179:     if !ar.DeletionTimestamp.IsZero() {\n180:         return r.handleDeletion(ctx, ar)\n181:     }\n182: \n183:     // 3. 确保 Finalizer 存在\n184:     if err := r.ensureFinalizer(ctx, ar); err != nil {\n185:         return ctrl.Result{}, err\n186:     }\n187: \n188:     // 4. 同步期望状态\n189:     result, err := r.sync(ctx, ar)\n190:     if err != nil {\n191:         return ctrl.Result{}, err\n192:     }\n193: \n194:     // 5. 更新 Status\n195:     if err := r.updateStatus(ctx, ar); err != nil {\n196:         return ctrl.Result{}, err\n197:     }\n198: \n199:     return result, nil\n200: }\n201: ```\n202: \n203: ### 5.2 状态机\n204: \n205: ```\n206: ┌─────────┐    Create    ┌─────────┐\n207: │  None   │ ──────────> │ Pending │\n208: └─────────┘             └────┬────┘\n209:                              │\n210:                         PodCreated\n211:                              │\n212:                              v\n213:                        ┌─────────┐\n214:                        │ Running │\n215:                        └────┬────┘\n216:                             │\n217:                     Failed/Succeeded\n218:                             │\n219:                             v\n220:                       ┌──────────┐\n221:                       │ Terminated│\n222:                       └──────────┘\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## 6. 实施计划\n228: \n229: | 阶段 | 内容 | 预估工时 |\n230: |------|------|----------|\n231: | P1 | 搭建 controller-runtime 框架 | 2d |\n232: | P2 | 实现 AgentRuntime 控制器 | 3d |\n233: | P3 | 实现 CodeInterpreter 控制器 | 2d |\n234: | P4 | 单元测试 + 集成测试 | 2d |\n235: | P5 | Leader Election + 监控 | 1d |\n236: \n237: **总计**: ~10 人天\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ## 7. 参考文档\n242: \n243: - controller-runtime: https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\n244: - client-go 生成的代码: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n245: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-007 |\n| Module | pkg/workloadmanager |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\n实现一个 Kubernetes Reconciler 控制器，用于管理 `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API 组下的自定义资源：\n\n- **AgentRuntime**: 管理 Agent 运行时实例的生命周期\n- **CodeInterpreter**: 管理代码解释器实例的生命周期\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775866995983,"end":1775866996004}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866996009,"sessionID":"ses_28614b83affeyVWDYwcMvR6UKe","part":{"id":"prt_d79ebdabc001KFuAVu4Q60Vn4I","messageID":"msg_d79eba6a10013Z1gFa5Irc35Kw","sessionID":"ses_28614b83affeyVWDYwcMvR6UKe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d0ee2a8353654b8c96c267674b03c931","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014: Valkey Storage Implementation\n2: \n3: Module: `pkg/store`\n4: Language: Go\n5: Size: S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Implement Valkey-backed session storage for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking. This delta implements `store_valkey.go` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### REQ-001: Valkey Client Initialization\n18: \n19: **GIVEN** Valkey backend needs configuration  \n20: **WHEN** initializing Valkey client  \n21: **THEN** environment variables shall be read correctly\n22: \n23: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n24: \n25: ```go\n26: // Scenario 1: Valkey address required\n27: GIVEN VALKEY_ADDR environment variable set to \"localhost:6379\"\n28: WHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\n29: THEN returned ClientOption.InitAddress SHALL be [\"localhost:6379\"]\n30: \n31: // Scenario 2: Valkey address comma-separated\n32: GIVEN VALKEY_ADDR environment variable set to \"host1:6379,host2:6379\"\n33: WHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\n34: THEN returned ClientOption.InitAddress SHALL be [\"host1:6379\", \"host2:6379\"]\n35: \n36: // Scenario 3: Valkey password passed\n37: GIVEN VALKEY_PASSWORD environment variable set to \"secret\"\n38: WHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\n39: THEN returned ClientOption.Password SHALL be \"secret\"\n40: \n41: // Scenario 4: Password required by default\n42: GIVEN VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty and VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED unset\n43: WHEN Valkey store initializes\n44: THEN initialization SHALL fail with password required error\n45: \n46: // Scenario 5: Password optional when disabled\n47: GIVEN VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty and VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"\n48: WHEN Valkey store initializes\n49: THEN initialization SHALL succeed with empty password\n50: \n51: // Scenario 6: VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED case insensitive\n52: GIVEN VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"FALSE\"\n53: WHEN checking password requirement\n54: THEN comparison SHALL be case-insensitive\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### REQ-002: Valkey Optional Client Flags\n60: \n61: **GIVEN** optional Valkey client configuration  \n62: **WHEN** building client options  \n63: **THEN** optional flags shall be set correctly\n64: \n65: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n66: \n67: ```go\n68: // Scenario 1: DisableCache enabled\n69: GIVEN VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"\n70: WHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\n71: THEN ClientOption.DisableCache SHALL be true\n72: \n73: // Scenario 2: DisableCache ignored when not true\n74: GIVEN VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"yes\"\n75: WHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\n76: THEN ClientOption.DisableCache SHALL NOT be set\n77: \n78: // Scenario 3: ForceSingleClient enabled\n79: GIVEN VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"\n80: WHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\n81: THEN ClientOption.ForceSingleClient SHALL be true\n82: \n83: // Scenario 4: Both flags enabled\n84: GIVEN VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\" and VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"\n85: WHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\n86: THEN ClientOption.DisableCache SHALL be true\n87: AND ClientOption.ForceSingleClient SHALL be true\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ### REQ-003: Valkey Store Struct\n93: \n94: **GIVEN** Valkey implementation needs state  \n95: **WHEN** defining valkeyStore struct  \n96: **THEN** required fields shall be present\n97: \n98: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n99: \n100: ```go\n101: // Scenario 1: valkeyStore struct definition\n102: GIVEN pkg/store/store_valkey.go\n103: WHEN reading the struct\n104: THEN valkeyStore SHALL contain cli valkey.Client\n105: AND valkeyStore SHALL contain sessionPrefix string\n106: AND valkeyStore SHALL contain expiryIndexKey string\n107: AND valkeyStore SHALL contain lastActivityIndexKey string\n108: \n109: // Scenario 2: sessionPrefix value\n110: GIVEN valkeyStore instance\n111: WHEN initialized\n112: THEN sessionPrefix SHALL be \"session:\"\n113: \n114: // Scenario 3: expiryIndexKey value\n115: GIVEN valkeyStore instance\n116: WHEN initialized\n117: THEN expiryIndexKey SHALL be \"session:expiry\"\n118: \n119: // Scenario 4: lastActivityIndexKey value\n120: GIVEN valkeyStore instance\n121: WHEN initialized\n122: THEN lastActivityIndexKey SHALL be \"session:last_activity\"\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ### REQ-004: Valkey Ping Implementation\n128: \n129: **GIVEN** connectivity verification needed  \n130: **WHEN** calling Ping  \n131: **THEN** Valkey PING command shall be issued\n132: \n133: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n134: \n135: ```go\n136: // Scenario 1: Ping returns nil on success\n137: GIVEN connected Valkey client\n138: WHEN Ping(ctx) is called\n139: THEN command B().Ping().Build() SHALL be executed\n140: AND return SHALL be nil when response equals \"PONG\"\n141: \n142: // Scenario 2: Ping returns error on failure\n143: GIVEN unreachable Valkey server\n144: WHEN Ping(ctx) is called\n145: THEN error from Valkey client SHALL be returned\n146: ```\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ### REQ-005: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID Implementation\n151: \n152: **GIVEN** session lookup needed  \n153: **WHEN** calling GetSandboxBySessionID  \n154: **THEN** correct Valkey GET shall be issued\n155: \n156: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n157: \n158: ```go\n159: // Scenario 1: Get existing session\n160: GIVEN key \"session:abc\" exists with valid JSON\n161: WHEN GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\n162: THEN command B().Get().Key(\"session:abc\").Build() SHALL be executed\n163: AND returned *types.SandboxInfo SHALL be unmarshaled from response bytes\n164: \n165: // Scenario 2: Get missing session\n166: GIVEN no key \"session:xyz\"\n167: WHEN GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"xyz\") is called\n168: THEN IsValkeyNil(response) SHALL be true\n169: AND method SHALL return nil, ErrNotFound\n170: \n171: // Scenario 3: JSON unmarshal error handled\n172: GIVEN key \"session:abc\" with invalid JSON\n173: WHEN GetSandboxBySessionID is called\n174: THEN unmarshal error SHALL be returned\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### REQ-006: Valkey StoreSandbox Implementation\n180: \n181: **GIVEN** new session creation needed  \n182: **WHEN** calling StoreSandbox  \n183: **THEN** atomic DoMulti shall execute\n184: \n185: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n186: \n187: ```go\n188: // Scenario 1: Reject nil sandbox\n189: GIVEN nil sandbox parameter\n190: WHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, nil) is called\n191: THEN error SHALL be returned indicating sandbox is nil\n192: \n193: // Scenario 2: Reject zero expiry\n194: GIVEN sandbox with ExpiresAt being zero time.Time{}\n195: WHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n196: THEN error SHALL be returned indicating invalid expiry\n197: \n198: // Scenario 3: DoMulti executes SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD activity\n199: GIVEN valid sandbox with SessionID \"s1\" and ExpiresAt t\n200: WHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n201: THEN DoMulti SHALL execute SETNX session:s1 <json>\n202: AND DoMulti SHALL execute ZADD session:expiry <t.Unix()> s1\n203: AND DoMulti SHALL execute ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix()> s1\n204: AND return SHALL be nil on success\n205: \n206: // Scenario 4: Reject duplicate session\n207: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" already exists\n208: WHEN StoreSandbox for same session ID is called\n209: THEN SETNX SHALL return 0\n210: AND error SHALL indicate session already exists\n211: \n212: // Scenario 5: DoMulti failure returns error\n213: GIVEN any command in DoMulti fails\n214: WHEN StoreSandbox processes results\n215: THEN error SHALL be returned\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ### REQ-007: Valkey UpdateSandbox Implementation\n221: \n222: **GIVEN** session data update needed  \n223: **WHEN** calling UpdateSandbox  \n224: **THEN** SET with XX shall be issued\n225: \n226: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n227: \n228: ```go\n229: // Scenario 1: Update existing session\n230: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\n231: WHEN UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n232: THEN command SET session:s1 <json> XX SHALL be built\n233: AND response.ToString() SHALL equal \"OK\"\n234: AND return SHALL be nil on success\n235: \n236: // Scenario 2: Update missing session\n237: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" does not exist\n238: WHEN UpdateSandbox is called\n239: THEN response.ToString() SHALL NOT equal \"OK\"\n240: AND error SHALL indicate key does not exist\n241: \n242: // Scenario 3: Indexes not modified\n243: GIVEN UpdateSandbox called\n244: WHEN executing the method\n245: THEN expiry ZSET SHALL NOT be modified\n246: AND last_activity ZSET SHALL NOT be modified\n247: ```\n248: \n249: ---\n250: \n251: ### REQ-008: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID Implementation\n252: \n253: **GIVEN** session removal needed  \n254: **WHEN** calling DeleteSandboxBySessionID  \n255: **THEN** atomic DoMulti cleanup shall execute\n256: \n257: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n258: \n259: ```go\n260: // Scenario 1: Delete existing session atomically\n261: GIVEN session \"s1\" exists with ZSET entries\n262: WHEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\") is called\n263: THEN DoMulti SHALL execute DEL session:s1\n264: AND DoMulti SHALL execute ZREM session:expiry s1\n265: AND DoMulti SHALL execute ZREM session:last_activity s1\n266: AND return SHALL be nil\n267: \n268: // Scenario 2: Delete missing session succeeds\n269: GIVEN session \"s1\" does not exist\n270: WHEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\") is called\n271: THEN DoMulti SHALL still execute DEL and ZREM\n272: AND return SHALL be nil (no error for missing)\n273: ```\n274: \n275: ---\n276: \n277: ### REQ-009: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes Implementation\n278: \n279: **GIVEN** expiry-based cleanup needed  \n280: **WHEN** calling ListExpiredSandboxes  \n281: **THEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE shall be used\n282: \n283: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n284: \n285: ```go\n286: // Scenario 1: Zero limit returns nil\n287: GIVEN limit <= 0\n288: WHEN ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n289: THEN return SHALL be nil, nil without Valkey calls\n290: \n291: // Scenario 2: ZRANGEBYSCORE with limit\n292: GIVEN ZSET session:expiry contains entries\n293: AND before = 2025-01-01T00:00:00Z\n294: AND limit = 10\n295: WHEN ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n296: THEN command Zrangebyscore session:expiry Min(\"-inf\") Max(\"<before.Unix()>\") Limit(0, 10) SHALL be built\n297: \n298: // Scenario 3: MGET for session data\n299: GIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session IDs [\"s1\", \"s2\"]\n300: WHEN loading sandbox data via loadSandboxesBySessionIDs\n301: THEN MGET session:s1 session:s2 SHALL be executed\n302: AND slice of *types.SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n303: \n304: // Scenario 4: Skip orphan ZSET entries\n305: GIVEN session ID \"orphan1\" in expiry ZSET but no session:orphan1 key\n306: WHEN MGET returns empty string for orphan1\n307: THEN that entry SHALL be skipped without error\n308: AND other valid sessions SHALL be returned\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ---\n312: \n313: ### REQ-010: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes Implementation\n314: \n315: **GIVEN** activity-based cleanup needed  \n316: **WHEN** calling ListInactiveSandboxes  \n317: **THEN** activity index shall be queried\n318: \n319: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n320: \n321: ```go\n322: // Scenario 1: ZRANGEBYSCORE on activity index\n323: GIVEN ZSET session:last_activity contains entries\n324: AND before and limit are valid\n325: WHEN ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n326: THEN command Zrangebyscore session:last_activity Min(\"-inf\") Max(\"<before.Unix()>\") Limit(0, limit) SHALL be built\n327: \n328: // Scenario 2: Session data loaded via MGET\n329: GIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session IDs\n330: WHEN processing results via loadSandboxesBySessionIDs\n331: THEN session data SHALL be loaded via single MGET command\n332: ```\n333: \n334: ---\n335: \n336: ### REQ-011: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity Implementation\n337: \n338: **GIVEN** activity timestamp update needed  \n339: **WHEN** calling UpdateSessionLastActivity  \n340: **THEN** existence check shall precede ZADD\n341: \n342: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n343: \n344: ```go\n345: // Scenario 1: Reject empty session ID\n346: GIVEN empty sessionID string\n347: WHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at) is called\n348: THEN error SHALL indicate session ID is empty\n349: \n350: // Scenario 2: Use current time when at is zero\n351: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\n352: AND at is zero time.Time{}\n353: WHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\n354: THEN time.Now() SHALL be used for the score\n355: \n356: // Scenario 3: Update activity for existing session\n357: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\n358: AND at is non-zero time\n359: WHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\n360: THEN EXISTS session:s1 SHALL return int64 1\n361: AND Zadd session:last_activity Score(<at.Unix()>).Member(\"s1\") SHALL be executed\n362: AND return SHALL be nil\n363: \n364: // Scenario 4: Reject missing session\n365: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" does not exist\n366: WHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\n367: THEN EXISTS SHALL return int64 0\n368: AND ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n369: ```\n370: \n371: ---\n372: \n373: ### REQ-012: Valkey Close Implementation\n374: \n375: **GIVEN** graceful shutdown needed  \n376: **WHEN** calling Close  \n377: **THEN** Valkey client shall be closed\n378: \n379: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n380: \n381: ```go\n382: // Scenario 1: Close succeeds\n383: GIVEN connected Valkey client\n384: WHEN Close() is called\n385: THEN cli.Close() SHALL be invoked\n386: AND return SHALL be nil\n387: ```\n388: \n389: ---\n390: \n391: ### REQ-013: MGET Optimization Implementation\n392: \n393: **GIVEN** multiple sandbox documents need loading  \n394: **WHEN** calling loadSandboxesBySessionIDs  \n395: **THEN** single MGET shall be used\n396: \n397: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n398: \n399: ```go\n400: // Scenario 1: Build keys from session IDs\n401: GIVEN session IDs [\"abc\", \"def\"]\n402: WHEN loadSandboxesBySessionIDs is called\n403: THEN keys SHALL be [\"session:abc\", \"session:def\"]\n404: \n405: // Scenario 2: Single MGET command\n406: GIVEN keys list built\n407: WHEN executing load\n408: THEN B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build() SHALL be executed\n409: \n410: // Scenario 3: Process MGET results\n411: GIVEN MGET returns [bytes1, emptyVal, bytes2]\n412: WHEN processing results\n413: THEN bytes1 SHALL be unmarshaled to SandboxInfo\n414: AND emptyVal SHALL be skipped (IsValkeyNil or empty string)\n415: AND bytes2 SHALL be unmarshaled to SandboxInfo\n416: AND result SHALL have 2 entries\n417: \n418: // Scenario 4: Slot comment for deployment\n419: GIVEN loadSandboxesBySessionIDs implementation\n420: WHEN reading the code\n421: THEN comment SHALL indicate keys should be in same slot for cluster deployment\n422: ```\n423: \n424: ---\n425: \n426: ### REQ-014: Valkey Store Type Selection\n427: \n428: **GIVEN** multiple backend options  \n429: **WHEN** initializing store with valkey  \n430: **THEN** Valkey backend shall be selected\n431: \n432: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n433: \n434: ```go\n435: // Scenario 1: Valkey store type\n436: GIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"valkey\"\n437: WHEN initStore runs\n438: THEN Valkey implementation SHALL be selected\n439: \n440: // Scenario 2: Case-insensitive valkey\n441: GIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"VALKEY\"\n442: WHEN initStore runs\n443: THEN Valkey implementation SHALL be selected\n444: \n445: // Scenario 3: Valkey requires VALKEY_ADDR\n446: GIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"valkey\"\n447: AND VALKEY_ADDR not set\n448: WHEN initStore runs\n449: THEN initialization SHALL fail with error indicating VALKEY_ADDR required\n450: \n451: // Scenario 4: Invalid store type still fails\n452: GIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"unknown\"\n453: WHEN initStore runs\n454: THEN initialization SHALL fail with unsupported store type error\n455: ```\n456: \n457: ---\n458: \n459: ### REQ-015: Valkey Command Builder Usage\n460: \n461: **GIVEN** Valkey client uses command builder pattern  \n462: **WHEN** executing operations  \n463: **THEN** correct builder chain shall be used\n464: \n465: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n466: \n467: ```go\n468: // Scenario 1: Ping builder\n469: GIVEN Ping method\n470: WHEN building command\n471: THEN B().Ping().Build() SHALL be used\n472: \n473: // Scenario 2: Get builder\n474: GIVEN GetSandboxBySessionID method\n475: WHEN building command\n476: THEN B().Get().Key(key).Build() SHALL be used\n477: \n478: // Scenario 3: Set builder with NX\n479: GIVEN StoreSandbox SETNX\n480: WHEN building command\n481: THEN B().Set().Key(key).Value(value).Nx().Build() SHALL be used\n482: \n483: // Scenario 4: Set builder with XX\n484: GIVEN UpdateSandbox\n485: WHEN building command\n486: THEN B().Set().Key(key).Value(value).Xx().Build() SHALL be used\n487: \n488: // Scenario 5: ZADD builder\n489: GIVEN ZADD operations\n490: WHEN building command\n491: THEN B().Zadd().Key(key).Score(score).Member(member).Build() SHALL be used\n492: \n493: // Scenario 6: ZRANGEBYSCORE builder\n494: GIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE operations\n495: WHEN building command\n496: THEN B().Zrangebyscore().Key(key).Min(min).Max(max).Limit(offset, count).Build() SHALL be used\n497: \n498: // Scenario 7: DEL builder\n499: GIVEN DEL operations\n500: WHEN building command\n501: THEN B().Del().Key(key).Build() SHALL be used\n502: \n503: // Scenario 8: ZREM builder\n504: GIVEN ZREM operations\n505: WHEN building command\n506: THEN B().Zrem().Key(key).Member(member).Build() SHALL be used\n507: \n508: // Scenario 9: EXISTS builder\n509: GIVEN EXISTS operations\n510: WHEN building command\n511: THEN B().Exists().Key(key).Build() SHALL be used\n512: \n513: // Scenario 10: MGET builder\n514: GIVEN MGET operations\n515: WHEN building command\n516: THEN B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build() SHALL be used\n517: ```\n518: \n519: ---\n520: \n521: ### REQ-016: ZSET Score Semantics\n522: \n523: **GIVEN** sorted set indexes need numeric scores  \n524: **WHEN** adding to ZSET  \n525: **THEN** Unix timestamps shall be used as scores\n526: \n527: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n528: \n529: ```go\n530: // Scenario 1: Expiry score on store\n531: GIVEN sandbox with ExpiresAt timestamp\n532: WHEN StoreSandbox adds to expiry ZSET\n533: THEN score SHALL be float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n534: \n535: // Scenario 2: Last activity score on store\n536: GIVEN StoreSandbox called\n537: WHEN adding to last_activity ZSET\n538: THEN score SHALL be float64(time.Now().Unix())\n539: \n540: // Scenario 3: Last activity score on update\n541: GIVEN UpdateSessionLastActivity called with time at\n542: WHEN adding to last_activity ZSET\n543: THEN score SHALL be float64(at.Unix())\n544: ```\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ### REQ-017: Valkey Response Handling\n549: \n550: **GIVEN** Valkey client returns typed responses  \n551: **WHEN** processing response  \n552: **THEN** correct type extraction shall be used\n553: \n554: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n555: \n556: ```go\n557: // Scenario 1: IsValkeyNil check\n558: GIVEN Valkey response\n559: WHEN checking for nil/missing\n560: THEN resp.IsValkeyNil() SHALL be used for nil detection\n561: \n562: // Scenario 2: ToString for OK check\n563: GIVEN SET XX response\n564: WHEN checking success\n565: THEN resp.ToString() SHALL equal \"OK\" for success\n566: \n567: // Scenario 3: AsBytes for data\n568: GIVEN GET response\n569: WHEN extracting data\n570: THEN resp.AsBytes() SHALL return []byte for JSON unmarshal\n571: \n572: // Scenario 4: AsInt64 for EXISTS\n573: GIVEN EXISTS response\n574: WHEN checking existence\n575: THEN resp.AsInt64() SHALL return 1 for exists, 0 for missing\n576: \n577: // Scenario 5: AsStringSlice for ZRANGEBYSCORE\n578: GIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE response\n579: WHEN extracting member list\n580: THEN resp.AsStringSlice() SHALL return session ID strings\n581: ```\n582: \n583: ---\n584: \n585: ### REQ-018: Valkey DoMulti for Atomic Operations\n586: \n587: **GIVEN** multiple commands need atomic execution  \n588: **WHEN** executing pipelines  \n589: **THEN** DoMulti shall be used\n590: \n591: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n592: \n593: ```go\n594: // Scenario 1: StoreSandbox uses DoMulti\n595: GIVEN StoreSandbox method\n596: WHEN executing atomic store\n597: THEN DoMulti SHALL be used with SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD activity commands\n598: \n599: // Scenario 2: DeleteSandboxBySessionID uses DoMulti\n600: GIVEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID method\n601: WHEN executing atomic delete\n602: THEN DoMulti SHALL be used with DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM activity commands\n603: \n604: // Scenario 3: DoMulti returns slice of responses\n605: GIVEN DoMulti executed with N commands\n606: WHEN processing results\n607: THEN responses SHALL be slice of valkey.ValkeyResult with length N\n608: ```\n609: \n610: ---\n611: \n612: ### REQ-019: Unit Tests for Valkey Implementation\n613: \n614: **GIVEN** Valkey implementation needs test coverage  \n615: **WHEN** verifying functionality  \n616: **THEN** unit tests shall cover all methods\n617: \n618: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n619: \n620: ```go\n621: // Scenario 1: Valkey store tests exist\n622: GIVEN pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go\n623: WHEN running tests\n624: THEN Ping tests SHALL verify connectivity\n625: AND GetSandboxBySessionID tests SHALL verify lookup and not found\n626: AND StoreSandbox tests SHALL verify atomic creation and validation\n627: AND UpdateSandbox tests SHALL verify update semantics\n628: AND DeleteSandboxBySessionID tests SHALL verify cleanup\n629: AND ListExpiredSandboxes tests SHALL verify expiry query\n630: AND ListInactiveSandboxes tests SHALL verify activity query\n631: AND UpdateSessionLastActivity tests SHALL verify activity update\n632: \n633: // Scenario 2: Mock/miniredis used for tests\n634: GIVEN Valkey tests\n635: WHEN running tests\n636: THEN mock Valkey server or miniredis SHALL be used for test isolation\n637: ```\n638: \n639: ---\n640: \n641: ### REQ-020: Code Quality for Valkey\n642: \n643: **GIVEN** Valkey code needs to meet quality standards  \n644: **WHEN** running linting and validation  \n645: **THEN** code shall pass go vet and build\n646: \n647: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n648: \n649: ```go\n650: // Scenario 1: go vet passes\n651: GIVEN pkg/store/store_valkey.go\n652: WHEN running go vet ./pkg/store/...\n653: THEN zero issues SHALL be reported\n654: \n655: // Scenario 2: Build succeeds\n656: GIVEN pkg/store/store_valkey.go\n657: WHEN running go build ./pkg/store/...\n658: THEN build SHALL succeed without errors\n659: \n660: // Scenario 3: All tests pass\n661: GIVEN pkg/store/\n662: WHEN running go test ./pkg/store/...\n663: THEN all tests SHALL pass without failures\n664: ```\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## Implementation Files\n669: \n670: | File | Purpose |\n671: |------|---------|\n672: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation with all methods |\n673: | `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` | Valkey implementation tests |\n674: \n675: ---\n676: \n677: ## Dependencies\n678: \n679: | Package | Purpose |\n680: |---------|---------|\n681: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n682: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo types |\n683: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Logging (optional client flags) |\n684: | `context` | Request context |\n685: | `time` | Timestamp handling |\n686: | `strings` | Address splitting |\n687: | `strconv` | Bool parsing |\n688: | `os` | Environment variables |\n689: \n690: ---\n691: \n692: ## Valkey Operations Summary\n693: \n694: | Method | Valkey API / Builder |\n695: |--------|----------------------|\n696: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n697: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n698: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n699: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n700: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n701: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n702: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n703: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key → int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n704: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n705: \n706: ---\n707: \n708: ## ZSET Score Semantics\n709: \n710: | Index Key | Score Value | Member |\n711: |-----------|-------------|--------|\n712: | `session:expiry` | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` | session ID |\n713: | `session:last_activity` | `time.Now().Unix()` on store, `at.Unix()` on update | session ID |\n714: \n715: ---\n716: \n717: ## Environment Variables\n718: \n719: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n720: |----------|----------|---------|--------|\n721: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated addresses |\n722: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes (unless disabled) | - | Case-insensitive check for \"false\" |\n723: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | - | Set to \"false\" to disable password |\n724: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | - | ParseBool, must be true to enable |\n725: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | - | ParseBool, must be true to enable |\n726: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | `redis` | Case-insensitive |\n727: \n728: ---\n729: \n730: ## Validation Checklist\n731: \n732: - [ ] Valkey client initialized from environment with address splitting\n733: - [ ] Optional client flags (DisableCache, ForceSingleClient) supported\n734: - [ ] Password requirement configurable\n735: - [ ] valkeyStore struct with correct fields\n736: - [ ] Key naming uses \"session:\" prefix (same as Redis)\n737: - [ ] Ping verifies connectivity via B().Ping()\n738: - [ ] GetSandboxBySessionID handles found/not found via IsValkeyNil\n739: - [ ] StoreSandbox validates input and uses DoMulti for atomicity\n740: - [ ] UpdateSandbox uses SET XX and checks ToString() == \"OK\"\n741: - [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID uses DoMulti for cleanup\n742: - [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes uses Zrangebyscore builder\n743: - [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes uses Zrangebyscore builder\n744: - [ ] loadSandboxesBySessionIDs uses MGET for efficiency\n745: - [ ] UpdateSessionLastActivity checks EXISTS before Zadd\n746: - [ ] Close gracefully shuts down client\n747: - [ ] Store type selection supports \"valkey\" case-insensitively\n748: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n749: - [ ] Build succeeds without errors\n750: - [ ] All tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 750 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014: Valkey Storage Implementation\n\nModule: `pkg/store`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement Valkey-backed session storage for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking. This delta implements `store_valkey.go` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Valkey Client Initialization\n\n**GIVEN** Valkey backend needs configuration  \n**WHEN** initializing Valkey client  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775866995986,"end":1775866996007}}}}
