{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867164741,"sessionID":"ses_28614b83affeyVWDYwcMvR6UKe","part":{"id":"prt_d79ee7713001JcC95HfGyvOFlX","messageID":"msg_d79ec28ea001WnewcLWs7hLGgT","sessionID":"ses_28614b83affeyVWDYwcMvR6UKe","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-96501f2fcdae441f868a85d1cfa038a9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md","content":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n|--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n| `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n| `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n| `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n| `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── picod/\n│   ├── main.go              # PicoD entry point (implemented)\n│   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n├── router/\n│   ├── main.go              # Router entry point\n│   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n├── workloadmanager/\n│   ├── main.go              # WorkloadManager entry point\n│   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n└── agentd/\n│   ├── main.go              # Agentd entry point\n│   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n```\n\n### Binary Dependency Graph\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                            CLI Binaries                                       │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                               │\n│   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n│   │   picod   │     │   router  │     │workloadmanager│     │  agentd   │   │\n│   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n│        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n│        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n│   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n│   │ pkg/picod │     │pkg/router │     │pkg/workload   │     │pkg/agentd │   │\n│   │           │     │           │     │   manager     │     │           │   │\n│   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n│        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n│        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n│   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│   │                    Common Dependencies                                 │ │\n│   │  - k8s.io/klog/v2 (logging)                                           │ │\n│   │  - github.com/spf13/pflag (flags)                                     │ │\n│   │  - context, os, signal                                                │ │\n│   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                                                                               │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Deployment Model\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Kubernetes Cluster                          │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n│  │ router Deployment│    │workloadmanager   │                  │\n│  │    (Pod :8080)   │───▶│ Deployment       │                  │\n│  └──────────────────┘    │   (Pod :8080)    │                  │\n│           │              └──────────────────┘                  │\n│           │                      │                              │\n│           ▼                      ▼                              │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n│  │ Redis/Valkey     │    │  K8s API Server  │                  │\n│  │ (Session Store)  │    │  (CRDs, Pods)    │                  │\n│  └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘                  │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n│  │ agentd Deployment│    (Leader Election enabled)             │\n│  │  (Controller)    │                                           │\n│  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n│                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Sandbox Pod                                 │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n│  │ picod sidecar    │    (Local code execution)                │\n│  │   (Port 8080)    │                                           │\n│  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Common CLI Configuration Pattern\n\n```go\npackage main\n\ntype CLIConfig struct {\n    LogLevel    string `flag:\"log-level\" default:\"info\" usage:\"Log level (debug, info, warn, error)\"`\n    MetricsAddr string `flag:\"metrics-addr\" default:\"0\" usage:\"Metrics server address (0 to disable)\"`\n    HealthAddr  string `flag:\"health-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Health check server address\"`\n}\n```\n\n### PicoD CLI Configuration\n\n```go\npackage main\n\ntype PicoDConfig struct {\n    CLIConfig\n    Port         int    `flag:\"port\" default:\"8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n    Workspace    string `flag:\"workspace\" default:\"\" usage:\"Workspace directory path\"`\n    AuthEnabled  bool   `flag:\"auth-enabled\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable authentication\"`\n    MaxExecTime  int    `flag:\"max-exec-time\" default:\"30\" usage:\"Maximum execution time in seconds\"`\n    MaxFileSize  int64  `flag:\"max-file-size\" default:\"10485760\" usage:\"Maximum file size in bytes\"`\n    SanitizeRoot string `flag:\"sanitize-root\" default:\"\" usage:\"Root directory for path sanitization\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Router CLI Configuration\n\n```go\npackage main\n\ntype RouterConfig struct {\n    CLIConfig\n    Port                 string `flag:\"port\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int   `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"1000\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent requests\"`\n    Debug                bool   `flag:\"debug\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable debug mode\"`\n    EnableTLS            bool   `flag:\"enable-tls\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable TLS\"`\n    TLSCert              string `flag:\"tls-cert\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS certificate file\"`\n    TLSKey               string `flag:\"tls-key\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS key file\"`\n    StoreAddr            string `flag:\"store-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey address\"`\n    StorePassword        string `flag:\"store-password\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey password\"`\n    StoreType            string `flag:\"store-type\" default:\"redis\" usage:\"Store type (redis, valkey)\"`\n}\n```\n\n### WorkloadManager CLI Configuration\n\n```go\npackage main\n\ntype WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n    CLIConfig\n    Addr              string        `flag:\"addr\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP server address\"`\n    ReadTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"read-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP read timeout\"`\n    WriteTimeout      time.Duration `flag:\"write-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP write timeout\"`\n    IdleTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"idle-timeout\" default:\"90s\" usage:\"HTTP idle timeout\"`\n    ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration `flag:\"shutdown-timeout\" default:\"10s\" usage:\"Graceful shutdown timeout\"`\n    GCInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"gc-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Garbage collection interval\"`\n    GCOnceTimeout     time.Duration `flag:\"gc-once-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"Single GC run timeout\"`\n    Kubeconfig        string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n    MasterURL         string        `flag:\"master-url\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes API server URL\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Agentd CLI Configuration\n\n```go\npackage main\n\ntype AgentdConfig struct {\n    CLIConfig\n    IdleThreshold        time.Duration `flag:\"idle-threshold\" default:\"30m\" usage:\"Idle threshold for cleanup\"`\n    CheckInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"check-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Cleanup check interval\"`\n    MaxConcurrentCleanup int           `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"10\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent cleanups\"`\n    Namespaces           []string      `flag:\"namespace\" default:\"default\" usage:\"Namespaces to watch\"`\n    LeaderElection       bool          `flag:\"leader-election\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable leader election\"`\n    LeaderElectionID     string        `flag:\"leader-election-id\" default:\"agentcube-agentd\" usage:\"Leader election ID\"`\n    Kubeconfig           string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Binary Entry Point Interface\n\nEach binary follows this pattern:\n\n```go\npackage main\n\ntype Binary interface {\n    InitFlags() *Config\n    ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error\n    Run(ctx context.Context, cfg *Config) error\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n\nfunc main() {\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    flag.Parse()\n    \n    cfg := InitFlags()\n    if err := ValidateConfig(cfg); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"invalid config: %v\", err)\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n    \n    ctx, cancel := signal.NotifyContext(context.Background(), syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n    defer cancel()\n    \n    if err := Run(ctx, cfg); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"run error: %v\", err)\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Signal Handling Contract\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nfunc setupSignalHandler() context.Context {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n    \n    c := make(chan os.Signal, 2)\n    signal.Notify(c, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n    \n    go func() {\n        sig := <-c\n        klog.InfoS(\"received signal\", \"signal\", sig)\n        cancel()\n        \n        if sig == syscall.SIGKILL {\n            <-c\n            klog.InfoS(\"received second signal, forcing exit\")\n            os.Exit(1)\n        }\n    }()\n    \n    return ctx\n}\n```\n\n### Health Check Contract\n\n```go\npackage main\n\ntype HealthChecker interface {\n    Live() bool\n    Ready() bool\n}\n\nfunc (h *HealthServer) Start(addr string) error {\n    mux := http.NewServeMux()\n    mux.HandleFunc(\"/live\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        if h.Live() {\n            w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n            w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n        } else {\n            w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n        }\n    })\n    mux.HandleFunc(\"/ready\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        if h.Ready() {\n            w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n            w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n        } else {\n            w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n        }\n    })\n    return http.ListenAndServe(addr, mux)\n}\n```\n\n### Flag Registration Contract\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nfunc InitFlags() *Config {\n    cfg := &Config{}\n    \n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n    \n    flag.StringVar(&cfg.LogLevel, \"log-level\", \"info\", \"Log level\")\n    flag.StringVar(&cfg.MetricsAddr, \"metrics-addr\", \"0\", \"Metrics address\")\n    flag.StringVar(&cfg.HealthAddr, \"health-addr\", \"\", \"Health address\")\n    \n    flag.Parse()\n    \n    return cfg\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Binary Implementation Details\n\n### 1. picod (cmd/picod/main.go)\n\n**Purpose**: Local code execution daemon running as a sidecar in sandbox pods.\n\n**Current Implementation** (pkg/picod/server.go:26-77):\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n\n    port := flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"HTTP listening port\")\n    workspace := flag.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Workspace directory path\")\n    flag.Parse()\n\n    config := &picod.Config{\n        Port:      *port,\n        Workspace: *workspace,\n    }\n\n    server, err := picod.NewServer(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n\n    if err := server.Run(context.Background()); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Endpoints**:\n| Path | Method | Purpose |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| `/health` | GET | Health check |\n| `/api/execute` | POST | Execute code |\n| `/api/files` | POST | Upload file |\n| `/api/files` | GET | List files |\n| `/api/files/*path` | GET | Download file |\n\n### 2. router (cmd/router/main.go)\n\n**Purpose**: Session routing and reverse proxy for agent/code interpreter invocations.\n\n**Implementation Template**:\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n    \n    cfg := &RouterConfig{}\n    flag.StringVar(&cfg.Port, \"port\", \":8080\", \"HTTP listening port\")\n    flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreAddr, \"store-addr\", \"\", \"Redis/Valkey address\")\n    flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreType, \"store-type\", \"redis\", \"Store type\")\n    flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests, \"max-concurrent\", 1000, \"Max concurrent requests\")\n    flag.BoolVar(&cfg.Debug, \"debug\", false, \"Enable debug mode\")\n    flag.Parse()\n    \n    ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n    \n    store, err := initStore(cfg)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    sessionManager := router.NewSessionManager(store)\n    jwtManager := router.NewJWTManager()\n    \n    server := router.NewServer(&router.Config{\n        Port:                 cfg.Port,\n        MaxConcurrentRequests: cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests,\n        Debug:                cfg.Debug,\n    }, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, klog.Logger{})\n    \n    if err := server.Start(ctx); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"router error: %v\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Endpoints**:\n| Path | Method | Purpose |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n| `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Agent invocation proxy |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Code interpreter proxy |\n\n### 3. workloadmanager (cmd/workloadmanager/main.go)\n\n**Purpose**: Workload manager HTTP server for sandbox lifecycle management.\n\n**Implementation Template**:\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n    \n    cfg := &WorkloadManagerConfig{}\n    flag.StringVar(&cfg.Addr, \"addr\", \":8080\", \"HTTP server address\")\n    flag.DurationVar(&cfg.ReadTimeout, \"read-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Read timeout\")\n    flag.DurationVar(&cfg.WriteTimeout, \"write-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Write timeout\")\n    flag.DurationVar(&cfg.GCInterval, \"gc-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"GC interval\")\n    flag.StringVar(&cfg.Kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Kubeconfig path\")\n    flag.Parse()\n    \n    ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n    \n    k8sClient, err := workloadmanager.NewK8sClient(cfg.Kubeconfig, cfg.MasterURL)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create k8s client: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    store, err := initStore(cfg)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    server := workloadmanager.NewHTTPServerWithClients(\n        workloadmanager.Config{\n            Addr:            cfg.Addr,\n            ReadTimeout:     cfg.ReadTimeout,\n            WriteTimeout:    cfg.WriteTimeout,\n            ShutdownTimeout: cfg.ShutdownTimeout,\n        },\n        klog.Logger{},\n        k8sClient,\n        store,\n    )\n    \n    server.RegisterHandler(\"health\", workloadmanager.NewHealthHandler())\n    server.RegisterHandler(\"sandbox\", workloadmanager.NewSandboxHandler(k8sClient, store))\n    \n    server.GracefulShutdown()\n    \n    errCh := server.Start()\n    select {\n    case err := <-errCh:\n        klog.Fatalf(\"workloadmanager error: %v\", err)\n    case <-ctx.Done():\n        server.Stop(context.Background())\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Endpoints**:\n| Path | Method | Purpose |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n| `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n| `/sandboxes` | POST | Create sandbox |\n| `/sandboxes/:id` | GET | Get sandbox |\n| `/sandboxes/:id` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n\n### 4. agentd (cmd/agentd/main.go)\n\n**Purpose**: Kubernetes controller for idle resource cleanup using controller-runtime.\n\n**Implementation Template**:\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n    \n    cfg := &AgentdConfig{}\n    flag.DurationVar(&cfg.IdleThreshold, \"idle-threshold\", 30*time.Minute, \"Idle threshold\")\n    flag.DurationVar(&cfg.CheckInterval, \"check-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"Check interval\")\n    flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup, \"max-concurrent\", 10, \"Max concurrent cleanups\")\n    flag.BoolVar(&cfg.LeaderElection, \"leader-election\", true, \"Enable leader election\")\n    flag.StringVar(&cfg.LeaderElectionID, \"leader-election-id\", \"agentcube-agentd\", \"Leader election ID\")\n    flag.Parse()\n    \n    k8sConfig, err := ctrl.GetConfig()\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to get k8s config: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(k8sConfig, ctrl.Options{\n        LeaderElection:          cfg.LeaderElection,\n        LeaderElectionID:        cfg.LeaderElectionID,\n        LeaderElectionNamespace: \"default\",\n    })\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create manager: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    if err := agentd.SetupIdleCleanupController(mgr, cfg); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to setup controller: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    klog.InfoS(\"starting agentd controller\")\n    if err := mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"controller error: %v\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories\n\n| Category | Description | Action |\n|----------|-------------|--------|\n| `ErrConfigInvalid` | Configuration validation failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n| `ErrStoreConnect` | Store connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n| `ErrK8sConnect` | Kubernetes connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n| `ErrServerStart` | HTTP server start failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n| `ErrSignalReceived` | Graceful shutdown triggered | Log info, cancel context |\n| `ErrShutdownTimeout` | Shutdown exceeded timeout | Log warning, force exit |\n\n### Error Handling Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc handleStartupError(component string, err error) {\n    if errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n        klog.InfoS(\"shutdown requested\")\n        return\n    }\n    \n    if errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGTERM) || errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGINT) {\n        klog.InfoS(\"received termination signal\", \"signal\", err)\n        return\n    }\n    \n    klog.ErrorS(err, \"startup failure\", \"component\", component)\n    os.Exit(1)\n}\n```\n\n### Graceful Shutdown Sequence\n\n```\n1. Signal received (SIGTERM/SIGINT)\n2. Cancel main context\n3. Stop accepting new requests\n4. Wait for in-flight requests (timeout configurable)\n5. Close store connections\n6. Close K8s client connections\n7. Exit with code 0\n```\n\n### Validation Errors\n\n```go\nfunc ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error {\n    if cfg.Port <= 0 || cfg.Port > 65535 {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid port: %d\", cfg.Port)\n    }\n    \n    if cfg.IdleThreshold < 0 {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid idle threshold: %v\", cfg.IdleThreshold)\n    }\n    \n    if cfg.CheckInterval < 0 {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid check interval: %v\", cfg.CheckInterval)\n    }\n    \n    if cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup < 0 {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid max concurrent cleanup: %d\", cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup)\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Flag Parsing Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestInitFlags(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name     string\n        args     []string\n        expected *Config\n    }{\n        {\n            name: \"default values\",\n            args: []string{},\n            expected: &Config{\n                Port:           8080,\n                LogLevel:       \"info\",\n                IdleThreshold:  30 * time.Minute,\n            },\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"custom port\",\n            args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\"},\n            expected: &Config{\n                Port:          9000,\n            },\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"multiple flags\",\n            args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\", \"-debug\", \"true\"},\n            expected: &Config{\n                Port:  9000,\n                Debug: true,\n            },\n        },\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            fs := flag.NewFlagSet(\"test\", flag.ContinueOnError)\n            cfg := &Config{}\n            setupFlags(fs, cfg)\n            \n            err := fs.Parse(tt.args)\n            require.NoError(t, err)\n            \n            assert.Equal(t, tt.expected.Port, cfg.Port)\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### Signal Handler Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestSignalHandler(t *testing.T) {\n    ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n    \n    syscall.Kill(syscall.Getpid(), syscall.SIGTERM)\n    \n    select {\n    case <-ctx.Done():\n        assert.True(t, true)\n    case <-time.After(5 * time.Second):\n        t.Fatal(\"signal handler did not cancel context\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### Config Validation Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestValidateConfig(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name        string\n        config      *Config\n        expectError bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name: \"valid config\",\n            config: &Config{\n                Port:          8080,\n                IdleThreshold: 30 * time.Minute,\n            },\n            expectError: false,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"invalid port\",\n            config: &Config{\n                Port: -1,\n            },\n            expectError: true,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"invalid idle threshold\",\n            config: &Config{\n                IdleThreshold: -1 * time.Minute,\n            },\n            expectError: true,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            err := ValidateConfig(tt.config)\n            if tt.expectError {\n                assert.Error(t, err)\n            } else {\n                assert.NoError(t, err)\n            }\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### Binary Startup Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestBinaryStartup(t *testing.T) {\n    if testing.Short() {\n        t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n    }\n    \n    binary := buildBinary(t, \"picod\")\n    \n    cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \"18080\")\n    cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n    cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n    \n    err := cmd.Start()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    defer cmd.Process.Kill()\n    \n    assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n        resp, err := http.Get(\"http://localhost:18080/health\")\n        if err != nil {\n            return false\n        }\n        defer resp.Body.Close()\n        return resp.StatusCode == http.StatusOK\n    }, 10*time.Second, 100*time.Millisecond)\n}\n```\n\n#### Graceful Shutdown Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestGracefulShutdown(t *testing.T) {\n    binary := buildBinary(t, \"router\")\n    \n    cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \":18080\", \"-store-type\", \"memory\")\n    cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n    cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n    \n    err := cmd.Start()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    waitForHealthy(t, \"http://localhost:18080/health/live\")\n    \n    syscall.Kill(cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGTERM)\n    \n    done := make(chan error, 1)\n    go func() {\n        done <- cmd.Wait()\n    }()\n    \n    select {\n    case err := <-done:\n        assert.NoError(t, err)\n    case <-time.After(15 * time.Second):\n        t.Fatal(\"binary did not shutdown within timeout\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Build Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestBuildAllBinaries(t *testing.T) {\n    binaries := []string{\"picod\", \"router\", \"workloadmanager\", \"agentd\"}\n    \n    for _, binary := range binaries {\n        t.Run(binary, func(t *testing.T) {\n            cmd := exec.Command(\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", \"/tmp/\"+binary, \"./cmd/\"+binary)\n            output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n            assert.NoError(t, err, \"build output: %s\", output)\n            \n            assert.FileExists(t, \"/tmp/\"+binary)\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Metrics\n\n### Prometheus Metrics\n\n```go\nvar (\n    startupDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n        prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_binary_startup_duration_seconds\",\n            Help: \"Time taken for binary startup\",\n        },\n        []string{\"binary\"},\n    )\n    \n    shutdownDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n        prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_binary_shutdown_duration_seconds\",\n            Help: \"Time taken for graceful shutdown\",\n        },\n        []string{\"binary\"},\n    )\n    \n    configReloadCount = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_binary_config_reload_total\",\n            Help: \"Number of configuration reloads\",\n        },\n        []string{\"binary\"},\n    )\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Binary | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `PORT` | picod, router, workloadmanager | HTTP port override |\n| `WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n| `STORE_ADDR` | router, workloadmanager | Redis/Valkey address |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | router, workloadmanager | Store backend type |\n| `KUBECONFIG` | workloadmanager, agentd | Kubernetes config path |\n| `LOG_LEVEL` | all | Log level override |\n\n### Command-Line Flags Summary\n\n| Flag | Default | Purpose |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| `-port` | 8080 | HTTP listening port |\n| `-workspace` | current dir | Workspace directory (picod) |\n| `-idle-threshold` | 30m | Idle cleanup threshold (agentd) |\n| `-check-interval` | 5m | Cleanup check interval (agentd) |\n| `-leader-election` | true | Enable leader election (agentd) |\n| `-kubeconfig` | in-cluster | Kubernetes config path |\n| `-debug` | false | Enable debug mode (router) |\n| `-metrics-addr` | 0 | Prometheus metrics address |\n\n---\n\n## Build Configuration\n\n### Go Module\n\n```go\n// go.mod\nmodule github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n\ngo 1.24\n\nrequire (\n    github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.x\n    github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.x\n    k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.x\n    sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.x\n)\n```\n\n### Makefile Targets\n\n```makefile\n.PHONY: build clean\n\nbuild:\n\tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n\tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n\tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n\tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n\nclean:\n\trm -rf bin/\n\nbuild-picod:\n\tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n\nbuild-router:\n\tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n\nbuild-workloadmanager:\n\tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n\nbuild-agentd:\n\tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n```\n\n### Docker Build\n\n```dockerfile\n# Dockerfile for picod\nFROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY . .\nRUN go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod\n\nFROM alpine:3.19\nCOPY --from=builder /picod /picod\nENTRYPOINT [\"/picod\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [x] `cmd/picod/main.go` - PicoD entry point (implemented)\n- [ ] `cmd/router/main.go` - Router entry point\n- [ ] `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` - WorkloadManager entry point\n- [ ] `cmd/agentd/main.go` - Agentd entry point\n- [ ] Common signal handling package\n- [ ] Common flag validation utilities\n- [ ] Health check server integration\n- [ ] Metrics server integration\n- [ ] Unit tests for flag parsing\n- [ ] Unit tests for config validation\n- [ ] Integration tests for binary startup\n- [ ] Integration tests for graceful shutdown\n- [ ] Makefile build targets\n- [ ] Docker build configurations\n- [ ] Helm deployment manifests\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/spf13/pflag` | v1.x | POSIX/GNU-style flags |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.x | Controller utilities (agentd) |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.x | HTTP framework (picod, router) |\n| `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | v5.x | HTTP framework (workloadmanager) |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics |"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/picod/main.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/server.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":156,"character":52},"end":{"line":156,"character":63}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/jwt_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":439,"character":5},"end":{"line":439,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"function \"contains\" is unused","tags":[1]}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":26,"character":9},"end":{"line":26,"character":9}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field TLSCert"},{"range":{"start":{"line":27,"character":8},"end":{"line":27,"character":8}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field TLSKey"},{"range":{"start":{"line":29,"character":7},"end":{"line":29,"character":7}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field Debug"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-